'''Vent Haven Museum''' is the world's only museum of ventriloquial figures and memorabilia. The museum is in Fort Mitchell, Kentucky, just 5 miles south of [[Cincinnati]], [[Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venthavenmuseum.net/faq/faq1.html |title=Vent Haven Museum FAQ |publisher=Vent Haven Museum |date=2008 |accessdate=2008-01-15}} (webarchive)</ref>

Vent Haven Museum was founded by William Shakespeare Berger, a Cincinnati businessman and amateur [[ventriloquist]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.venthavenmuseum.net/faq/faq2.html |title=Vent Haven Museum FAQ |publisher=Vent Haven Museum |date=2008 |accessdate=2008-01-06}} (webarchive)</ref>

